(Characters, incidents, and dates do not match historical facts.)

3
00:00:09,870 --> 00:00:12,001
I would like to speak.

4
00:00:12,241 --> 00:00:15,440
It is about the Princess' marriage.

5
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:17,781
You will never get your own way.

6
00:00:17,781 --> 00:00:19,841
I am offering a chance.

7
00:00:19,841 --> 00:00:23,850
A chance for you and your offspring to save your lives.

8
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:25,621
They are looking for the King's son-in-law.

9
00:00:26,051 --> 00:00:27,821
The Princess will marry.

10
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:31,121
I will always be on your side no matter what.

11
00:00:31,121 --> 00:00:33,291
I cannot accept your feelings.

12
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:34,930
I must have her...

13
00:00:35,331 --> 00:00:37,100
even if that means I have to use force.

14
00:00:46,841 --> 00:00:49,341
(Episode 9)

15
00:00:49,341 --> 00:00:50,441
What is that sound?

16
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:53,450
They are officially announcing the royal wedding.

17
00:00:53,450 --> 00:00:55,710
They are calling the candidates into the palace.

18
00:00:59,380 --> 00:01:01,191
Princess.

19
00:01:02,021 --> 00:01:03,021
Come here quick.

20
00:01:03,890 --> 00:01:06,120
Look at this. Are they not pretty?

21
00:01:07,891 --> 00:01:09,391
What is all this?

22
00:01:09,391 --> 00:01:11,201
What do you think they are?

23
00:01:11,531 --> 00:01:13,001
We need to make a dress for your wedding.

24
00:01:13,201 --> 00:01:14,400
Not just a wedding dress.

25
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:17,240
From head to toe, you will need so many ornaments.

26
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,840
They have not yet selected her husband-to-be.

27
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,240
- Why would you already... - How dare you to interrupt?

28
00:01:26,781 --> 00:01:28,551
I will not marry.

29
00:01:29,811 --> 00:01:31,751
Stop being so childish.

30
00:01:32,281 --> 00:01:33,721
The King gave the command,

31
00:01:33,721 --> 00:01:35,490
and the Five Tribe council decided on it.

32
00:01:36,051 --> 00:01:39,391
Do you not know this is a joy for the palace as well as the people?

33
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:41,730
The wedding where the bride is bartered...

34
00:01:42,861 --> 00:01:44,161
is not a joyous occasion.

35
00:01:47,801 --> 00:01:48,801
Princess.

36
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,100
How dare she?

37
00:01:51,941 --> 00:01:54,971
She has such an odd temperament.

38
00:01:57,111 --> 00:01:58,111
What now?

39
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,781
Where could she go other than to see her father?

40
00:02:04,551 --> 00:02:05,551
Princess.

41
00:02:17,231 --> 00:02:19,530
Many young men of noble birth...

42
00:02:20,370 --> 00:02:22,400
have applied to be your husband.

43
00:02:22,970 --> 00:02:25,571
The King is greatly blessed.

44
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:29,740
That means your influence is even greater.

45
00:02:31,511 --> 00:02:33,851
The influence that made this preposterous marriage...

46
00:02:34,551 --> 00:02:35,551
a possibility.

47
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,351
You have everything in the world.

48
00:02:39,881 --> 00:02:41,750
What more do you want?

49
00:02:44,361 --> 00:02:46,220
Tying me down with marriage...

50
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,391
will not benefit you at all.

51
00:02:48,761 --> 00:02:50,301
This is not for me.

52
00:02:51,231 --> 00:02:53,460
The marriage is for you, Princess.

53
00:03:01,271 --> 00:03:04,481
If you keep lashing out with stupidity and bravado,

54
00:03:05,111 --> 00:03:06,111
you might...

55
00:03:07,611 --> 00:03:11,120
follow in your mother's footsteps, and we cannot have that.

56
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:17,660
If your mother had acted appropriately for her status,

57
00:03:19,690 --> 00:03:22,060
she would not have died the way she did.

58
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:23,190
Shut your mouth.

59
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:27,370
How dare you mention my mother?

60
00:03:27,370 --> 00:03:28,870
We do not need any more...

61
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,271
misfortune in the royal family.

62
00:03:33,611 --> 00:03:36,011
The King saw my intentions...

63
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,710
and allowed your marriage.

64
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:11,780
A man crazed by jealousy...

65
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:15,150
killed his own wife and people.

66
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,391
Does he deserve to sit up here?

67
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,600
Father.

68
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,800
Did Go Won Pyo threaten you...

69
00:04:36,470 --> 00:04:38,300
into agreeing to my marriage?

70
00:04:39,741 --> 00:04:43,241
Do you fear his weapons that much?

71
00:04:44,311 --> 00:04:45,540
Why?

72
00:04:46,181 --> 00:04:47,980
You are King.

73
00:04:50,621 --> 00:04:53,951
I had a dream every night.

74
00:04:55,391 --> 00:04:59,491
A dream in which you and your mother die.

75
00:05:01,431 --> 00:05:06,001
A nightmare in which my people are slaughtered.

76
00:05:08,271 --> 00:05:10,331
I committed those dreadful deeds myself.

77
00:05:11,501 --> 00:05:13,501
How can I avoid punishment?

78
00:05:21,311 --> 00:05:23,311
When you returned to the palace,

79
00:05:24,751 --> 00:05:26,220
I was afraid.

80
00:05:27,951 --> 00:05:30,821
It felt as if my past wrongdoings had come back to life.

81
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,660
And I was also pleased.

82
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,501
Your mother...

83
00:05:39,131 --> 00:05:42,001
had given me a chance to atone.

84
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,470
If they had known how you felt,

85
00:05:49,741 --> 00:05:53,480
the Sunno Tribe migrants would also rejoice.

86
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:55,980
However...

87
00:05:57,621 --> 00:05:59,050
Before being the King,

88
00:05:59,951 --> 00:06:01,720
I am but a powerless father.

89
00:06:02,891 --> 00:06:04,191
I wanted to...

90
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:08,131
do whatever I could to protect you and the Crown Prince.

91
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:10,660
So...

92
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,600
is that what happened?

93
00:06:16,431 --> 00:06:17,840
Did Go Won Pyo...

94
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:21,371
threaten you with our lives?

95
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:30,951
I am sorry.

96
00:06:32,550 --> 00:06:35,650
I did all that I could,

97
00:06:37,261 --> 00:06:39,561
and yet I could not prevent your marriage.

98
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,470
Princess.

99
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:52,741
Will you forgive me?

100
00:06:56,071 --> 00:06:57,071
Father.

101
00:07:54,431 --> 00:07:56,071
The herb gatherer is gone,

102
00:07:56,071 --> 00:07:57,900
and a young noble is here.

103
00:07:58,501 --> 00:07:59,741
Your clothes...

104
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:02,241
did more than just change your looks.

105
00:08:09,081 --> 00:08:11,350
Mok Tae Seon, a silk merchant from Jami Province.

106
00:08:12,821 --> 00:08:14,951
I just have to say I am his son?

107
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:17,590
Creating a fake identity is not all.

108
00:08:18,621 --> 00:08:21,460
You will be questioned to see if you studied all the classics.

109
00:08:21,991 --> 00:08:23,491
When given a theme,

110
00:08:23,491 --> 00:08:24,931
you must also write a poem.

111
00:08:27,331 --> 00:08:28,831
I do not need to do that.

112
00:08:28,831 --> 00:08:31,001
Do you truly think that is possible?

113
00:08:32,601 --> 00:08:34,641
Even if you apply as a candidate,

114
00:08:35,241 --> 00:08:39,540
General Go will end up marrying the Princess.

115
00:08:40,910 --> 00:08:42,450
That will not happen.

116
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,820
I cannot let Ga Jin be forced into a marriage.

117
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:51,060
We feel the same.

118
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:54,461
You are in love?

119
00:09:00,001 --> 00:09:01,001
Fate.

120
00:09:03,271 --> 00:09:05,200
She and I are destined to be together.

121
00:09:07,511 --> 00:09:09,440
So I cannot let her marry.

122
00:09:10,810 --> 00:09:12,141
I will do whatever it takes.

123
00:09:25,621 --> 00:09:28,560
They turned us into traitors so they could get rid of us.

124
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,700
I was a fool.

125
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,601
I underestimated Go Won Pyo.

126
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,841
For Father.

127
00:09:42,241 --> 00:09:43,871
And for Ga Jin.

128
00:09:46,741 --> 00:09:48,310
Go Won Pyo.

129
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:52,751
I will kill you and die myself.

130
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:24,420
Read the theme for the poem in the envelope.

131
00:10:39,361 --> 00:10:41,670
I heard that General Go did not apply.

132
00:10:42,231 --> 00:10:44,040
Does that mean we have a chance?

133
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:47,001
You are such a fool. Do you think your father or mine...

134
00:10:47,001 --> 00:10:49,540
sent us with hopes to become the King's in-law?

135
00:10:50,271 --> 00:10:52,580
It is what the Five Tribe council commanded.

136
00:10:52,810 --> 00:10:54,580
What do you mean by that?

137
00:10:55,381 --> 00:10:58,680
They will fail all of us and when they think there is no one worthy,

138
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:00,991
they will recommend General Go as if there is no substitute.

139
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:03,491
If his eldest son were to enter the selection process,

140
00:11:03,491 --> 00:11:05,920
how would Gochuga manage to judge fairly?

141
00:11:06,221 --> 00:11:09,790
Darn it. I am here to stand in the background, then.

142
00:11:10,631 --> 00:11:13,731
Let us go and get drunk with some girls after this.

143
00:11:14,001 --> 00:11:15,271
Next.

144
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,351
Here she is.

145
00:11:34,050 --> 00:11:35,991
I am here at your command.

146
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:38,420
Welcome.

147
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,790
I called her because...

148
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:45,131
she deals in herbs and also rare accessories.

149
00:11:45,131 --> 00:11:48,871
Hey. It was my idea to call her.

150
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:56,540
Do you feel better?

151
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:04,121
Both the Princess and Crown Prince act as they wish.

152
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:06,920
No one knows how stressful that is for me.

153
00:12:08,121 --> 00:12:11,221
I just hope my son has an uneventful future.

154
00:12:11,521 --> 00:12:14,330
I heard a talented fortune-teller has set up shop in the city.

155
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,930
Shall I ask for you?

156
00:12:17,731 --> 00:12:20,930
Fortune-telling? I have so many questions too.

157
00:12:21,570 --> 00:12:22,731
Where is he?

158
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:41,991
I brought some accessories that will suit you.

159
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:45,560
- Pick a few later. - No, thank you.

160
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:50,761
I will say this because I agreed to not keep secrets.

161
00:12:51,861 --> 00:12:54,060
I was unable to do as you asked.

162
00:12:57,001 --> 00:12:59,741
That young man. On Dal.

163
00:13:01,011 --> 00:13:04,680
The more I get to know him, the more intriguing he becomes.

164
00:13:05,141 --> 00:13:06,241
What about Dal?

165
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:10,011
He will be in the palace about now.

166
00:13:14,851 --> 00:13:15,920
Next.

167
00:13:22,131 --> 00:13:23,861
Oh!

168
00:13:24,660 --> 00:13:27,160
You look handsome and manly.

169
00:13:28,771 --> 00:13:30,771
- Take a seat. - Thank you.

170
00:13:31,601 --> 00:13:33,170
Let me see.

171
00:13:33,341 --> 00:13:36,070
Your family does not live within the Capital.

172
00:13:36,741 --> 00:13:38,440
You are from Jami Province.

173
00:13:39,141 --> 00:13:42,511
- That is so. - Your father is Mok Tae Seon.

174
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:45,920
Mok Tae Seon? I have heard that name.

175
00:13:46,721 --> 00:13:50,450
Is he not a merchant who sells silk...

176
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:51,961
and cotton goods?

177
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,221
What?

178
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:58,001
We are here to select the King's son-in-law...

179
00:13:58,001 --> 00:13:59,731
and a merchant's son applied?

180
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:02,400
Do not say more than you need.

181
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:05,670
A theme for a poem is in the envelope. Write something.

182
00:14:07,711 --> 00:14:08,910
I will do that.

183
00:14:13,841 --> 00:14:17,920
Lord Hae, it is such a pity.

184
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:20,481
Do you not think so?

185
00:14:21,450 --> 00:14:24,961
A merchant's son applied. That looks bad on us.

186
00:14:42,471 --> 00:14:43,711
Stop.

187
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:56,491
- What is it? - He hid his identity...

188
00:15:02,231 --> 00:15:03,891
to sneak into the palace.

189
00:15:05,731 --> 00:15:07,530
He hid his identity?

190
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:10,800
Then is he not Mok Tae Seon's son?

191
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,101
That is true.

192
00:15:16,211 --> 00:15:17,981
Oh, dear...

193
00:15:20,111 --> 00:15:21,851
Then who are you?

194
00:15:29,091 --> 00:15:30,221
Dal.

